What is this project about?
--> This is an app that handles vacations in a company dynamically (i.e every company can customize their leaves).
    There are three types of users for this app: an owner, an admin and a normal user.
    the owner has all the privileges of an admin + the ability to approve of leave requests
    the admin can create new leave types and requests' responses
    a user can submit a leave request

How to run?
--> First create a .env file
    fill it with these variables
    DATABASE_URL = url to mysql database
    JWT_SECRET   = a secret string to encode authentication tokens
    EMAIL        = the email you wish to use to send emails to users
    EMAILPASS    = the password provided by your emailing service to authorize sending emails automatically
--> npm install
--> migrate prisma schema
--> npm start